SUPLINF.P:
This rule provides for a nearly automatic designation of any county in which drought conditions as reported in the U.S. Drought Monitor (
http://www.droughtmonitor.unl.edu
) meet the drought intensity value of at least D2 (DroughtГўВЂВ”Severe) for 8 consecutive weeks in any portion of the county. Further, any county that has a portion of its area in a drought intensity value of D3 (DroughtГўВЂВ”Extreme) or higher at any time during the growing season of the affected crops would be considered a disaster area.
